    Product(name="Black Shark 3 12GB RAM 128/256 GB 5G LTE", description="<h3>Black Shark 3 12GB RAM: Overview</h3> Xiaomi released the Black Shark 3 12GB RAM 5G in the March of 2020. It is the best gaming phone in the markets of Australia. Black Shark 3 has most of the latest technologies integrated. It can easily compete with the best of the bests like ROG phone 2, iPhone 11 Pro Max, and more. Shark 3 comes in different variations of internal storage. You get choices with 128GB and 256GB. Here we shall discuss both the UFS 3.0. Let's jump right into the values. <h5>Build:</h5> Xiaomi Black Shark 3 12GB RAM has a dimension of 168.7 x 77.3 x 10.4 mm, which is a large phone. You get an aluminum frame with a glass front and an aluminum back also. The Dual-SIM phone weighs about 222 grams with pop up triggers for gaming. [<a href=\"https://www.skyphonez.com.au/product/black-shark-2-pro-256gb-12gb-ram-4g-lte/\">Black Shark 2 Pro</a>] <h5>Display:</h5> The device has a 6.67 inches AMOLED capacitive touchscreen, which supports 16 M color depth. You will have the highest-graphics rendered easily with this display system. You almost get a bezel-less phone with an 82.4% screen-to-body ratio. Xiaomi Black Shark 3 has a 1080 x 2400 pixels resolution with an aspect ratio of 20:9. It doesn't include the highest refresh rate but enough to satisfy your needs. You get a 90Hz refresh rate on the display with 395 PPI density. Xiaomi advertises 500 nits of brightness, which is pretty sleek. The display system has HDR10 support for enhanced details on the display. Now you can enjoy UHD quality on every frame. You get an always-on display along with the fast-Fingerprint sensor under the display. <h5>Platform:</h5> Xiaomi Black Shark 3 12GB operates on an Android 10.0 with an Octa-core Kryo 585 CPU. The platform integrates the flagship Qualcomm SM8250 Snapdragon 865 (7 nm ) chipset and Adreno 650 GPU. With this combination, you can play any game in the Play store with ease and efficiency. The device can render high-quality images and applications with the best graphics requirements. The platform is well suited for capturing high-definition videos and shooting stunning pictures. But the Shark 3 Pro being a Gaming Phone, Xiaomi doesn't focus on the cameras much. The phone has a UFS 3.0 with a 12GB RAM capacity. The sad part of the storage is you cannot expand the storage capacity. But you do not have to worry much like the storage capacity is ever going to be full. <h5>Camera:</h5> The phone has a 64 MP wide-angle camera, a 13 MP ultrawide-angle camera, and a 5 MP depth sensor. You can shoot decent photos and record videos at 4k at 30 and 60 fps and 1080p at up to 240fps. The camera doesn't have gyro-EIS, which is not a problem. You are buying a gaming phone, not a camera-centric phone. There is a single 20 MP wide-angle phone for video calling and selfies. You can shoot 1080p at 30fps, which is pretty decent on a gaming phone. You also get HDR support with the front camera. <h5>Battery:</h5> The phone has a Non-removable Li-Po 4720 mAh battery and supports Fast charging 65W. You can charge the phone 100% in 38 minutes. It also supports the Magnetic charging up to18W. The battery system supports unlimited gaming with fast charging. <h5>Sound:</h5> You get an immersive environment with the loudspeakers with Stereo speaker support. The gaming and listening to music will have an enhancement with the stereo speakers. The good part of the sound on the phone is the 3.5 mm jack port. You can connect wired in-ear headphones and earphones for the lowest latency while gaming. [<a href=\"https://www.skyphonez.com.au/product/xiaomi-mi-10-lite-5g-128gb-6gb-ram-eu-model/\">Xiaomi Mi 10 Lite</a>] <h5>Extras:</h5> The connectivity features on the phone include dual-SIM that support 5G networks. You will have faster data transfer rates while streaming and playing games. Other connectivity features are WLAN [ Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac/ax, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot ] and Bluetooth 5.0 (A2DP, LE, aptX HD, aptX Adaptive). GPS with A-GPS, GLONASS, GALILEO, QZSS, BDS, and USB 2.0, Type-C 1.0 reversible connectors are interesting features to have on your phone.", product_imgs_amt=2, category="gadgets", instant_buy=False, add_on=True, advert=True, shipping_speed=1, shipping_usa=False, verified=False, merchant_id=1),
